cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper deals with the generation of cryptographic keys in vehicular ad hoc networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network security (cs.CR). The focus on vehicular networks suggests a subcategory of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The incorporation of temporal variability attributes and scatterers' mobility suggests a systems and control (cs.SY) subcategory. Finally, the use of turbo codes for error correction suggests a multimedia (cs.MM) subcategory.
